// Man page for chmod
// XFIX1.0: -r uses engine recurse (fast). Per-node denial reporting is on chown/chgrp/chog.
manChmod="CHMOD(8)                         X Shell Manual                         CHMOD(8)

<b>NAME</b>
    chmod - change the access permissions of a file|directory
<b>SYNOPSIS</b>
    <b>chmod </b> [<b>-r|-R</b>] <b>[u|g|o][|-][wrx] </b><b>FILE</b> [FILE...]
    <b>chmod </b> [<b>-r|-R</b>] <b>000-777 </b><b>FILE</b> [FILE...]
    <b>find</b> PATTERN | <b>chmod</b> <b>MODE</b>
<b>DESCRIPTION</b>
    Modify file and folder permissions for read, write, and execute access.
    Permissions apply to owner, group, and others. Use symbolic (urwx) or octal (777).
    Recursive -r applies to all subdirectories. Octal: 4=read, 2=write, 1=execute.
    Supports glob patterns for multiple files: <b>*.sh</b>, <b>bin/*</b>, <b>src/**/*.src</b>
    Accepts filenames from stdin via pipe — mode is passed as the argument.
<b>OPTIONS</b>
    <b>-r, -R</b>
    Recursive mode
    Apply to directory tree

    <b>[u|g|o][|-][rwx]</b>
    Symbolic permissions
    Add or remove flags

    <b>000-777</b>
    Octal permissions
    Three-digit mode
<b>EXAMPLE:</b>
    <color=#e4ff34># Symbolic Mode</color>
    <b>chmod ow file.txt</b>
    Add write for others

    <b>chmod g-r file.txt</b>
    Remove group read

    <b>chmod u-rx document.txt</b>
    Remove user readexec

    <color=#e4ff34># Octal Mode</color>
    <b>chmod 645 document.txt</b>
    Owner:rw, Group:r, Other:rx

    <b>chmod 755 script.sh</b>
    Standard executable

    <b>chmod 600 secret.txt</b>
    Owner readwrite only

    <color=#e4ff34># Pipe Support</color>
    <b>find *.src | chmod 755</b>
    Make all matched files executable

    <b>find /home/user/scripts *.sh | chmod u+x</b>
    Add execute for owner on all scripts
<b>SEE ALSO</b>
    <b>chown</b>, <b>chgrp</b>, <b>chog</b>"